## {#2d-extension data-menu-title="Extending to 2D"}

[Extending to two dimensions]{.slide-title}

<hr>

The same idea applies with two or more predictors.

- Add $X_3 = X_1^2 + X_2^2$ to the circular data
- The inner cluster (small $X_3$) separates from the outer ring (large $X_3$) in 3D
- A flat plane in 3D produces a **circular** boundary back in the original 2D space

